            <page>
                <exercise workspace="1in">
                    <title>Motivation: Determinants</title>
                    <statement>
                        <p>
                            
                        </p>
                    </statement>
                    <solution>
                        <p>
                            The determinant is a numerical property of a matrix that holds a lot of information
                            (e.g., is the matrix invertible, how does it behave as a transformation). We'll develop
                            multiple ways to view the determinant in this section.
                        </p>
                    </solution>
